Yang Haodong Delivers a Lecture on the Spirit of the 6th Plenary Session of the 19th CPC Central Committee and the Provincial Party Congress at Malanshan, Drawing Strength from the Centennial Struggle of the Party - Hunan Daily, December 10 (All-media Reporter Gong Baiwei) - According to the unified arrangement of the Provincial Party Committee, on the morning of December 10, Yang Haodong, Standing Committee Member and Minister of Propaganda of the Provincial Party Committee, held an interactive lecture at Malanshan Video and Cultural Creative Park. He conducted in-depth studies and implementation of the spirit of the 6th Plenary Session of the 19th CPC Central Committee, the important speeches, instructions, and directives of General Secretary Xi Jinping for Hunan, and the spirit of the 12th Provincial Party Congress. Yang Haodong expounded on the core essence and practical requirements of the plenary spirit comprehensively and systematically from three aspects: ideals, beliefs and original mission, self-revolution and the great youth of the Party, and the Party's leaders and theories, combining his own insights and personal experiences. He pointed out that it is necessary to integrate the spirit of the plenary session with the important speeches, instructions, and directives of General Secretary Xi Jinping for Hunan, and the spirit of the Provincial Party Congress, to enhance the ideological, political, and action consciousness of defending the "two establishments" and achieving the "two safeguards," and unswervingly follow the direction pointed out by General Secretary Xi Jinping. During the interactive exchange session, grassroots cadre representatives, enterprise representatives, and youth representatives raised questions on the relationship between the three historical resolutions, how to understand the decisive significance of the "two establishments," how cultural enterprises should grasp the orientation, and how the youth of the new era can draw strength from the centennial history of the Party. Yang Haodong answered each question with plain language and vivid examples. He earnestly advised the young Party members to draw strength for progress from the Party's hundred-year struggle, closely unite around the Party Central Committee, unswervingly follow the Party, and use their youth to fulfill their responsibilities and undertake their duties.
